			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2008</a> paper:</span><br><i>Formalization and Rule-Based Transformation of EMF Ecore-Based Models</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/BernhardSchätz.html">Bernhard Schätz</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-00434-6_15">10.1007/978-3-642-00434-6_15</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4b.html"><span class="tagM">T4B: Horizontal Transformation</span></a><ul><li> It formalizes and applies rule-based transformations over EMF Ecore-based models, i.e., model-to-model rewriting.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5d.html"><span class="tagL">T5D: Formal Methods</span></a><ul><li> The paper emphasizes a formalization of the transformation framework and rules for rigor.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3b.html"><span class="tagL">T3B: Transformation Languages</span></a><ul><li> The rule-based transformation approach effectively defines a transformation language/notation for Ecore models.
</li></ul></li></ul>
